data.meta_description: View of Flor Silvestre as she sings and performs on her horse during the rodeo at the California State Fair. Governor Ronald Reagan and his family sit in the grandstand. On Reagan's left is the wife of the Executive Secretary for the fair, Mrs. William P. Clark. This was the last fair held at the old fair grounds.
